@swingeveryday @Andreas2112 @RichardSimmons1 $AMD $XLNX $AAPL $NET Simple answer is, it&#39;s not Fed Taper itself that&#39;s bullish or bearish, it the Fed Taper combined with EXPECTATIONS GOING INTO TAPERING that makes the event bullish. The market saw taper coming from a mile away and has already priced it into bonds (and subsequently stocks). If you&#39;re only just reacting to Fed Tapering, you&#39;re TOO LATE man. You&#39;re already on the wrong side of this trade. Ever heard of &quot;sell the news&quot; lol

The market is now looking ahead and the current narrative is tapering means the beginning of the peak in inflations and this is bullish for stocks and bonds (lower rates)

Final point, just look at 2014 when the Fed last tapered. Markets went straight up
